records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The State moves to delete the enhancer of within 1000 feet of park on count 1.  Motion granted.
GUILTY Plea entered to the amended charge in count 1 of deliver heroin.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is one (1) years initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision, consecutive to other sentences presently being served in case no: 10 CF 6189 and 14 CF 3651.  
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs of $518.00;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs;
6) No possession, consumption, selling or distribution of  any illegal drugs or alcohol;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) Mainatin fulltime employment and/or schooling;
9) Follow all rules of supervision;
10) Any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.
The defendant has credit for 8 days.  
Minutes.
